---
description: LLM backend conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

# LLM backend

- Separate prompts from Python code when possible.
- Keep prompt templates in a dedicated folder.
- Never hardcode secrets or API keys.
- Log model name, prompt version, and latency when relevant.
- Make provider wrappers replaceable.
- Prefer structured outputs over free-form parsing.

# Reliability

- Add retries/timeouts for external model calls.
- Handle malformed model outputs defensively.
